      "comment": "JOLSON AL (5) is on debut today with Chris Parnham sticking from his latest trial where he was strong from the front. He looks to get every chance from the favourable alley and his trials suggest he has good upside about him. Wouldn't surprise to see him make a statement on debut. FREE TO FLY (10) was just fair in her debut campaign, though her latest trial was very impressive. Pike liked what he saw there and hops on board for her return. This inside draw is perfect and if she can run up to her trial performance, she'll be hard to hold out. JOYOH (9) comes here off an 84-day break and hasn't trialled since a 0.6L defeat as favourite at Pinjarra. Back to 1200m here, but she'll be flying home late in the race. FINADO (2) is third-up now off a long break and bumped into a good winner here last time out. Can be in the finish once again. ADMIRE BELLE (11) will be better for the debut effort and is not to be discounted.",
